  "lyrics": "Oh, this summer's breaking me in And son, all the things we had Were erected and I'll, I'll breathe again I'll see again I'll see this world through the eyes of another I will come again I'll see again I'll feel again I'll find you through the summer's end The summer's end I see you walking And I know there'll be more I'm afraid of The summer's end I'll see you again I'll see you standing there looking just as beautiful, my friend I know this can't be the end There's more waiting for me And you move There's more to see More to experience and I'll be okay And the summer's end I'll know the fences and I'll Have a better sense of time For you I'll not break you down Make you go through all that time Be around We'll be around We'll come again After the summer's end, yeah We'll be around There's more to this There's more to this All after the summer's end Chains they tacitly lift me up It's like a panic attack I erupt, emotions and dreams and life and what it seems Do I get another shot at what we seem? Then I understand it's hard that you breathe Yeah, it's right that you waste If you sit there not being true Turn your own faith in place I'll see you then There's more to life than any other Thing that you could ever dream of Where I'm being true Where I'm wanting to Dream with me a little louder There's more to life There's more to life than the dark to finding grey A matter of where you just start To look left And you're here Yeah That's how the end of the summer feels With you You're looking great in that tan Your bathing suit's on fire, baby I can't stop but to misbehave",
